%% Diagram type: flowchart TD
%% What this answers: "What is the authoring + retirement lifecycle for a
%%   .mmd / .svg diagram pair? Walk: new diagram -> render -> commit pair ->
%%   CI verifies SHA-256 of re-render matches committed SVG -> merge or
%%   block (GLD-001 stale render); on retirement BOTH files MUST be deleted."
%% Authoritative source: spec/26-gitlogs-diagrams/01-diagram-conventions/00-overview.md
%% Audience: contributors authoring/retiring diagrams; CI auditors verifying drift.
%% Entry point: read 00-overview.md "Diagram pairing rule" section first; this
%%   diagram is the visual canon for that rule. Drift detector: GLD-001 in CI.
flowchart TD
    A[New Diagram Authored] --> B[Author X.mmd]
    B --> C[Run: mmdc -i X.mmd -o X.svg]
    C --> D[Commit Both Files Same PR]
    D --> E[CI: Re-render X.mmd]
    E --> F{SHA-256 of new SVG == committed SVG?}
    F -- No --> G[Block: GLD-001 stale render]
    F -- Yes --> H[Merge]
    H --> I{Diagram Retired?}
    I -- Yes --> J[Delete BOTH .mmd and .svg]
